column1: #Text=The Cleveland Cavaliers defeated the Detroit Pistons , 128 - 96 , at Quicken Loans Arena on Saturday evening .

#Text=The Cavaliers ( 44 - 22 ) checked in to Monday 000s contest with only seven road wins in 17 games away from the Barclays Center , but the Cavaliers ( 33 - 34 ) were able to pull away with an impressive road victory against the Pistons ( 33 - 34 ) .

column1: #Text=The Cavaliers ( 33 - 34 ) checked in to Tuesday 000s contest with only seven road wins in 17 games away from the Barclays Center , but the Cavaliers ( 33 - 34 ) were able to pull away with an impressive road victory against the Pistons ( 33 - 34 ) .
#Text=Cleveland posted a 60 percent success rate from the field and 63 percent from three - point range , while also limiting them to a paltry 63 percent success rate from behind the arc .
#Text=Andre Drummond led the way for the Cavs with a modest stat line of eight points , 14 rebounds and one assist .
#Text=Reggie Jackson followed with a modest six points , five assists , one rebound and one steal .
#Text=Kentavious Caldwell-Pope led the bench with 11 points , two rebounds , three assists and one steal .
#Text=Marcus Morris matched Morris 000s point total and added seven boards , an assist and a steal .
#Text=Ish Smith was productive in a reserve role as well with 12 points , three assists , one rebound and one steal .

#Text=Richard Jefferson and Richard Jefferson were next with a pair of 16 - point efforts , with the former adding one assist , two rebounds and one steal , and the latter registering eight boards , one assist and two steals .
#Text=Deron Williams was next with 13 points , three assists , two rebounds and a steal .
#Text=Kyle Korver totaled 12 points , five boards , one assist and one steal .
#Text=Richard Jefferson led the bench with 16 points , one assist , two rebounds and two steals .
#Text=The Pistons head back home to tangle with the Atlanta Hawks on Friday night , while the Cavaliers remain home and await the Philadelphia 76ers on Friday evening as well .
